---
import ProductDetailLayout from "../../layouts/ProductDetailLayout.astro";

const gallery = ["gallery/gis/gis-02.png"];
---

<ProductDetailLayout
  title="RIP/RIF GIS Outlet Bushing"
  productCode="QXFG(P)RGW"
  voltage="40.5kV - 550kV"
  current="1000A - 8000A"
  description="Product Item: QXFG(P)RGW\nRated Voltage: 40.5kV - 550kV\nRated Current: 1000A - 8000A\nDry-type Condenser GIS Bushing\nRIP GIS Outlet Bushing\nRIF GIS Outlet Bushing"
  mainImage="product-gis-bushing.png"
  galleryImages={gallery}
>

  <div class="tech-section-title">Main Technical Index</div>
  <div class="tech-diagram">
    <img src="/assets/qxelectric/tech-diagram-gis.png" alt="GIS Outlet Bushing Technical Diagram" loading="lazy" />
  </div>
  <table class="tech-table">
    <thead><tr><th colspan="7">Main Technical Index</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td colspan="2">System Nominal Voltage (kV)</td><td>66</td><td>110</td><td>220</td><td>330</td><td>500</td></tr>
      <tr><td colspan="2">Rated Voltage (Highest Voltage for Equipment) (kV)</td><td>72.5</td><td>126</td><td>252</td><td>363</td><td>550</td></tr>
      <tr><td rowspan="2">Power Frequency Withstand Voltage (kV/min)</td><td>Dry</td><td>140</td><td>230</td><td>460</td><td>595</td><td>710</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Wet</td><td>140</td><td>230</td><td>460</td><td>535</td><td>-</td></tr>
      <tr><td rowspan="2">Lightning Impulse Withstand Voltage</td><td>Full Wave</td><td>325</td><td>550</td><td>1050</td><td>1175</td><td>1550</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Chopped Wave</td><td>357.5</td><td>605</td><td>1155</td><td>1292.5</td><td>1705</td></tr>
      <tr><td colspan="2">Switching Impulse Withstand Voltage (kV)</td><td>-</td><td>-</td><td>850</td><td>950</td><td>1175</td></tr>
      <tr><td rowspan="2">Dielectric Dissipation Factor</td><td>Maximum</td><td colspan="5">The value at 1.05Um/√3 shall not exceed 0.4%.</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Increment</td><td colspan="5">The increment between 1.05Um/√3 and Um shall not exceed 0.1%.</td></tr>
      <tr><td colspan="2">Test Terminal Insulation Level (kV/min)</td><td colspan="5">3</td></tr>
      <tr><td rowspan="2">Partial Discharge Level (pC)</td><td>Um</td><td colspan="5">≤10</td></tr>
      <tr><td>1.05Um/√3</td><td colspan="5">≤5</td></tr>
      <tr><td colspan="2">Pressure Tightness Test</td><td colspan="5">0.65MPa/24h, no leakage.</td></tr>
      <tr><td colspan="2">Short-Time Withstand Current</td><td colspan="5">Magnitude: 25 times rated current, max 100kA. Duration: 2s.</td></tr>
      <tr><td colspan="2">Rated Frequency (Hz)</td><td colspan="5">50</td></tr>
      <tr><td colspan="2">Outdoor Shed</td><td colspan="5">Outdoor sheds with alternating long and short profiles for anti-pollution. Nominal creepage distance complies with GB/T 26218.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <!-- Cantilever Load Table -->
  <table class="tech-table">
    <thead><tr><th colspan="5">Cantilever Withstand Load (N)</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td rowspan="2">Rated Voltage (kV)</td><td colspan="4">Rated Current (A)</td></tr>
      <tr><td>≤800</td><td>1000-1600</td><td>2000-2500</td><td>≥3150</td></tr>
      <tr><td>72.5</td><td>2000N</td><td>2000N</td><td>3150N</td><td>4000N</td></tr>
      <tr><td>126</td><td>3150N</td><td>3150N</td><td>4000N</td><td>4000N</td></tr>
      <tr><td>252</td><td>4000N</td><td>4000N</td><td>5000N</td><td>5000N</td></tr>
      <tr><td>363</td><td>4000N</td><td>4000N</td><td>5000N</td><td>5000N</td></tr>
      <tr><td>550</td><td>4000N</td><td>4000N</td><td>5000N</td><td>5000N</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <div class="content-block">
    <p>This bushing provides a direct, reliable connection between overhead lines (or other outdoor equipment) and SF6-insulated metal-enclosed switchgear (GIS).</p>
  </div>

  <div class="tech-section-title">Product Advantages</div>
  <div class="content-block">
    <p><strong>True Solid Dielectric Solution:</strong> Our RIF or RIP bushings eliminate SF6 gas entirely from the bushing body, solving the endemic problems of gas leakage, pressure monitoring, and costly maintenance.</p>
    <p><strong>All-Angle Installation &amp; Low-Temperature Operation:</strong> The solid design allows installation at any angle and remains fully functional in extremely low temperatures (below -40°C), where SF6 gas can liquefy and cause insulation failure.</p>
    <p><strong>Enhanced Safety:</strong> Removes the risk of explosion due to loss of gas pressure or internal flashover.</p>
    <p><strong>Custom Design:</strong> Adaptable to various GIS interfaces and environmental conditions.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="tech-section-title">Suitable Service Conditions for Bushings</div>
  <div class="content-block">
    <p><strong>Altitude:</strong> Applicable for installations at or below 2000m above sea level.</p>
    <p><strong>Ambient Temperature:</strong> Suitable for -50 °C to +50 °C.</p>
    <p><strong>Installation Angle:</strong> Can be installed at any angle.</p>
    <p><strong>Pollution Class:</strong> Suitable for heavily polluted areas, Class III or higher.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="tech-section-title">Ordering Information</div>
  <div class="content-block">
    <p>When placing an order, please specify:</p>
    <p><strong>1. Electrical Parameters:</strong> Rated voltage, rated current, rated frequency, external insulation creepage distance, internal insulation clearance, oil-end length, draw-lead length, CT mounting position length.</p>
    <p><strong>2. Environmental Parameters:</strong> Ambient temperature, altitude, pollution class.</p>
    <p><strong>3. Model Designation:</strong> The letter "F" in the model number indicates silicone rubber composite sheds. The absence of "F" indicates porcelain sheds.</p>
    <p><strong>Note:</strong> Custom flange and terminal dimensions available. Direct replacement bushings also supplied.</p>
  </div>

</ProductDetailLayout>
